data.text:
ANTHONY “TONY” QUINN, 65, died Saturday, February 10, 2024.

A native of Mendenhall, MS, Tony was a son of the late Walton “Webb” Pitts and Myrtis Conner Phillips. He grew up in the Lafayette and New Orleans areas of Louisiana. He lived in the Aiken area and was the owner of A. Quinn Tree Experts.

Surviving is his daughter, Carolyn Mae Quinn, Conway, SC; two sisters, Karen Little, Rocky Mount, NC, Crystal DeVane, Florence, SC; several nieces and nephews. In addition to his parents, he was preceded in death by his brother, David Phillips.

No local service will be held.

SHELLHOUSE – RIVERS FUNERAL HOME, 715 EAST PINE LOG RD., AIKEN, SC

To order memorial trees or send flowers to the family in memory of Anthony "Tony" Quinn, please visit our flower store.
